Defendant Steven M Barron in court with attorney Mark A. Pecora.  Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 2 is dismissed and read-in.  Count 3 is dismissed by operation of law.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

6 YEARS IMPRISONMENT - STAYED
  -  3 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION. 

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation - to be forward to City of Waukesha Police Department);

FINE:  $3,089.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

*D/L REVOCATION: 36 months

*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months

CONDITION TIME:  First 6 months Jail, straight (Credit - 3 days).  Last 6 months Huber with release for work and/or treatment.  Defendant remanded to custody forthwith.  

Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel:  completed

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
